{# Persistent-marker macros for queryable modules.

Two patterns are supported, matching the two distinct dispatcher shapes
discovered during the spikes:

  one_shot(name, params_decl, args_only, children)
    - Andropogon-style: the dispatcher fires ONCE, emits children, becomes
      a frozen marker. Used for InfloHead, Tiller, Panicle.

  Scape (and similar multi-iteration growers) cannot use a generic macro
  because the production body has multiple branches (still-growing vs
  done-growing). For those, write the persistent-marker logic inline:
  add an `expanded` or `done` boolean parameter, guard with
  `if done: produce <Name>(..., True)`, set `done=True` when the grower
  finishes. See rosette_scape_composite.lpy.j2's Scape rule for the
  worked example.

Macro arguments:
  name        : module name (string)
  params_decl : declaration form, e.g. "t_birth, max_height"
  args_only   : same params without type/default decoration, used in self-emit
                (Phase 0 they are identical; kept as separate arg in case
                Phase 1 adds typed declarations)
  children    : space-separated module emissions, e.g.
                "DiskFloret(t_birth, DISK_RADIUS_M, DISK_MAT) RayRing(RAY_COUNT, t_birth)"
#}

{% macro one_shot(name, params_decl, args_only, children) -%}
{{ name }}({{ params_decl }}, expanded) :
    if expanded:
        produce {{ name }}({{ args_only }}, True)
    produce {{ name }}({{ args_only }}, True) {{ children }}
{%- endmacro %}
